96910: Mourning Thrull.text_posted:
@UbdU01: I believe it should have had its ability errataed to lifelink, since the life gain triggers on [u]any[/u] damage, not just combat damage.

@Milliman: Yes, Mourning Thrull's life-stealing ability does in fact stack with lifelink, because it doesn't really have lifelink. So yeah, if you enchant it with [autocard]Lifelink[/autocard], you'd gain twice the damage dealt as life. However be careful - Mourning Thrull's life-stealing ability is a triggered ability, which means that it goes on the stack, as opposed to the static lifelink ability. This means two things: First off, your opponent can counter it with effects such as [autocard]Stifle[/autocard], and secondly, as opposed to with the lifelink ability, you won't get the life the instant the Thrull deals damage. If your Thrull is 100/1, you're at 1 life (with only the Thrull on the battlefield), and your opponents attacks you with 2 1/1 creatures, you'd die because your life goes to 0 before you gain the life from the Thrull's attack - as opposed to with lifelink, where you'd gain the 100 life from the Thrull's attack at the same time that you're dealt damage, which means that you wouldn't lose the game, and your life total would be 99 once the dust settled.

As for my own experiences with Mourning Thrull, I think it's absolutely brilliant. I've actually won games on the back of a Mourning Thrull paired with [autocard]Unspeakable Symbol[/autocard], and the power boost that BW received with the Eventide block only made it much more playable. Used in the right deck, for example paired with [autocard]Edge of the Divinity[/autocard], it can easily win you a couple of games fairly quickly.

